# CODEOWNERS - who must review changes to which paths.
#
# GitHub requires a listed owner's approval before a pull request touching a
# matching path can merge (when branch protection requires review). This is how
# the governance model is enforced mechanically: schema, tooling, and CI changes
# always need maintainer review, and can never auto-merge.
#
# Later, per-directory trust tiers for community contributors will be expressed
# by adding owners under /data/ - that is where the Trusted Contributor ladder
# (see GOVERNANCE.md) will apply. Today, everything is maintainer-owned.

# Default owner for everything.
*                   @KodeStar

# Maintainer-owned, always: schemas, tooling, internal packages, and CI/config.
# These define the contract and the pipeline - never auto-merge.
/schema/            @KodeStar
/cmd/               @KodeStar
/internal/          @KodeStar
/.github/           @KodeStar

# /data/ is where community trust tiers will apply (see GOVERNANCE.md). It is
# covered by the default owner above for now; Trusted Contributors' data-only
# pull requests auto-merge once required checks pass.
